text: Kathryn "Kat" Cammack (born February 16, 1988)Rep.-elect Kat Cammack (R-Fla.-03), The Hill, November 30, 2020. is an American politician and political advisor. She is a member of the United States House of Representatives from Florida's 3rd congressional district since 2021. Cammack was deputy chief of staff to Congressman Ted Yoho, who she replaced. Cammack is the youngest Republican woman elected to Congress in 2020; Sara Jacobs, a Democrat, is the only younger woman. ==References== Category:1988 births Category:Living people Category:United States representatives from Florida Category:Politicians from Denver Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
